WEBVTT

00:00:00.090 --> 00:00:03.093
<v ->So let's install the AWS CLI on mac</v>

00:00:03.093 --> 00:00:04.718
and for this we're just going to go on Google

00:00:04.718 --> 00:00:06.720
and make sure to choose a link

00:00:06.720 --> 00:00:10.240
installing the AWS CLI version 2 on macOS.

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:12.240
And then we're just going to follow the process,

00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:13.950
so we'll scroll down

00:00:13.950 --> 00:00:15.720
and see what they say.

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:18.220
And here is how to install it.

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:21.040
So we can just download a pkg file

00:00:21.040 --> 00:00:23.060
and this will be a graphical installer.

00:00:23.060 --> 00:00:24.713
So you download the pkg file.

00:00:25.719 --> 00:00:29.460
Then you click on continue, continue, continue

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:30.800
and you agree.

00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:32.857
Then you say, "Okay, install for all the users

00:00:32.857 --> 00:00:34.180
"on this computer."

00:00:34.180 --> 00:00:35.550
Click on continue

00:00:35.550 --> 00:00:37.560
and then click on install,

00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:41.000
and this goes ahead and installs the CLI on mac.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.050
So we wait for everything to be done,

00:00:43.050 --> 00:00:44.690
the files are being written.

00:00:44.690 --> 00:00:47.130
Okay, the installation is now successful

00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:48.910
and we'll move the installer to trash.

00:00:48.910 --> 00:00:50.400
And now to fill this out,

00:00:50.400 --> 00:00:52.100
you open a terminal on mac.

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:54.654
So you just go ahead and type, for example, "terminal",

00:00:54.654 --> 00:00:56.610
and this will give you a terminal app.

00:00:56.610 --> 00:00:58.930
Mine is called iterm on mac,

00:00:58.930 --> 00:01:01.170
which is a free terminal that you can use.

00:01:01.170 --> 00:01:05.850
And then you just type aws -- version

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:08.010
and if everything is going well,

00:01:08.010 --> 00:01:10.040
then it should give you back the version

00:01:10.040 --> 00:01:12.260
of the AWS executable.

00:01:12.260 --> 00:01:14.180
So let's wait for a little bit.

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:15.250
And we get the answer,

00:01:15.250 --> 00:01:17.330
AWS CLI 2.0.10,

00:01:17.330 --> 00:01:20.236
so that means that everything has been installed correctly.

00:01:20.236 --> 00:01:21.810
So that's it for this lecture.

00:01:21.810 --> 00:01:22.690
In case of issues,

00:01:22.690 --> 00:01:24.010
please have a look at this guide.

00:01:24.010 --> 00:01:25.610
It will have the answer for you.

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:26.530
And that's it for me.

00:01:26.530 --> 00:01:28.280
I will see you in the next lecture.